cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SE 

This paper is primarily focused on cybersecurity and machine learning methods for detecting anomalies in mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also extensively discusses the use of High Performance Extreme Learning Machine (HP-ELM) for malware detection, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is a sub-field of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in detecting malware, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
